hospice /ˈhɒspɪs/

(hospices) 

1. N-COUNT/N-IN-NAMES A hospice is a special hospital for people who are dying, where their practical and emotional needs are dealt with as well as their medical needs. 临终关怀医院 

例： ...a hospice for cancer patients. …一个癌症病人的临终关怀医院。 

2. ADJ Hospice care is medical care that is provided for people, either in a hospice or in their own home, when they are dying. 临终护理的 [ADJ n] 

例： Berle was diagnosed with colon cancer last year and had been under hospice care for the past few weeks. 去年伯利被诊断患有结肠癌，在过去的几周里他一直受到临终关怀护理。 

例： ...a hospice nurse. …一名从事临终护理的护士。

